    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/702.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Han Yang practically taken by Imperialists, according to report from Greene, who
                    adds that revolutionists declared they could not hold Wuchang and want three
                    days armistice to obtain the consent of the other provinces to accept Government
                    terms: retention of present dynasty. They desire, if other provinces refuse, to
                    be allowed to withdraw with their arms and save Wuchang from destruction. Greene
                    asks authority to join colleagues in employing good offices to make such
                    representations to Imperial forces. I do not approve such authorization but
                    await your instructions, and have so informed Greene.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
